<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>WWA | Women Who Actually</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,700;1,700&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  :root {
    --black: #0e0c0a;
    --cream: #f5f0e8;
    --warm-white: #faf8f4;
    --red: #BE0000; /* Arterial Red */
    --red-dark: #800000;
    --muted: #7a7060;
    --border: rgba(14,12,10,0.12);
  }
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
  body {
    background: var(--warm-white);
    color: var(--black);
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.6;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }
  nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 1.25rem 3rem;
    background: var(--warm-white);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .nav-logo {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--black);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .hero {
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    padding-top: 72px;
  }
  .hero-left {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 5rem 4rem 5rem 3rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--red);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .hero-headline {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(48px, 6vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .hero-headline em { font-style: italic; color: var(--red); }
  .hero-body {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 460px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .hero-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--cream);
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 1.25rem 2rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .hero-cta:hover { background: var(--red); }
  .hero-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    background: var(--cream);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .year-stamp {
    position: absolute;
    top: 3rem;
    right: 3rem;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 120px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: rgba(14,12,10,0.06);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .activation-banner {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--cream);
    padding: 1rem 3rem;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .manifesto {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .manifesto-label {
    padding: 5rem 3rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .manifesto-label span {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    writing-mode: vertical-rl;
    transform: rotate(180deg);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .manifesto-content { padding: 5rem 4rem 5rem 3rem; }
  .manifesto-content p {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.5vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .pillar { padding: 4rem 2rem; border-right: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .pillar:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .pillar-num { font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; color: var(--red); font-size: 11px; margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block; }
  .pillar-title { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 24px; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .join {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--cream);
    padding: 8rem 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 2rem 3rem;
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pillars { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a href="#" class="nav-logo">WWA.</a>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="#join" style="text-decoration:none; color:var(--black); font-family:'DM Mono'; font-size:11px;">Partner with us</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-left">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">The Power Network · Est. 2026</p>
    <h1 class="hero-headline">Women<br>who <em>actually</em><br>execute.</h1>
    <p class="hero-body">We are the antidote to the aesthetic-led collective. A high-utility infrastructure for women navigating the intersection of tech, leadership, and performance.</p>
    <a href="#join" class="hero-cta">Apply for Access <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-right">
    <div class="year-stamp">2026</div>
    <p style="font-family:'Playfair Display'; font-size:32px; font-style:italic;">"Systems over vibes."</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="activation-banner">
  <span>Current Activation: May 2026 Protocol</span>
  <span>Cohort: 19 Vanguards (Tech/Gov/Strategy)</span>
</div>

<section class="manifesto" id="manifesto">
  <div class="manifesto-label"><span>The Philosophy</span></div>
  <div class="manifesto-content">
    <p>We believe the highest-performing women are too busy building to ask for what they need. <strong>WWA</strong> provides the curation layer they don't have time to seek out.</p>
    <p>From the Amazon boardroom to the high-altitude trail, we equip the <em>Multitude</em> with the tools and networks required for relentless execution.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pillars">
  <div class="pillar">
    <span class="pillar-num">01</span>
    <h3 class="pillar-title">Curate</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px; color:var(--muted);">We vet high-performance tools and botanical protocols before they hit the mainstream.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="pillar">
    <span class="pillar-num">02</span>
    <h3 class="pillar-title">Connect</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px; color:var(--muted);">A non-indexed directory of decision-makers in Tech, Gov, and Business Leadership.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="pillar">
    <span class="pillar-num">03</span>
    <h3 class="pillar-title">Activate</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px; color:var(--muted);">In-person integration sprints designed for the modern matriarchy.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="pillar">
    <span class="pillar-num">04</span>
    <h3 class="pillar-title">Capital</h3>
    <p style="font-size:14px; color:var(--muted);">Directing resources into the hands of women who actually do the work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="join" id="join">
  <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display'; font-size:48px; margin-bottom:2rem;">Founded by Elizabeth Blockman</h2>
  <p style="max-width:600px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; color:rgba(245,240,232,0.6);">Elizabeth founded WWA to solve the "Discovery Gap" for women in high-stakes execution roles. Leveraging her background in business leadership and project management, she is building the infrastructure the Girl Boss era lacked.</p>
  <a href="mailto:elizabeth@womenwhoactually.com" class="hero-cta" style="background:var(--red);">Contact Partnerships</a>
</section>

<footer>
  <span>© 2026 Women Who Actually</span>
  <span>New York · DMV</span>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
